@sunker is part of the team that manages this code and knows much more about it than I do, so following his suggestion of adding it to the `_builder` file would be the preferred option.

Directly modifying the dimensionMap would have the disadvantage of being opaque and volatile. There would be no guarantee that the next time someone adds a dimension name with a space in that it would be handled correctly and we would have to resort to comments to explain why were deviating from CloudWatchs naming. It would also look weird in the query editor (the name is `dimension name` not `dimension name` despite us having to escape it as the latter when sending).

So out of your three options, 2 would be preferred.

@sakjur - I feel that #7360 and this are completely different issues. 

This is not about duplicate calls from two different sources. It is about duplicate calls for a single query. ( New panel, just one graph and just one query but three azure subscription calls )

Let me know if you need more details.

Also if someone is in need of a workaround, here's how I'm getting the from/to values:

```
let timeRange = requests | where $__timeFilter(timestamp) | summarize min = min(timestamp), max = max(timestamp);
let timeFrom = toscalar(timeRange | project min);
let timeTo = toscalar(timeRange | project max);
myRequest...
| make-series ... on timestamp in range(timeFrom, timeTo, $__interval)
| mv-expand ..., timestamp
```

